Uses of Package
com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.persistance

  • Packages that use com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.persistance 
    Package Description
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.api
    Contains APIs and supporting classes used by Coalesce
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework
    Contains classes used for creating a new instance of Coalesce for accessing and modifying Coalesce Entities.
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.jobs
    This package contains jobs that are threaded off to handled specific tasks.
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.persistance
    Contains base classes for creating persistors to store and retrieve Coalesce Entitites from different databases.
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.persistance.accumulo  
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.persistance.derby  
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.persistance.memory
    Contains a persister implementation that does not depend on any databases that can be used for unit testing.
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.persistance.neo4j  
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.persistance.postgres  
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.tasks
    This package contains tasks for each job for parallel processing.
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.framework.util
    Contains Coalesce utility classes.
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.notification.adminevent.impl
    This package contains a notification implementation that uses the admin events within an OSGi environment.
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.notification.impl
    This package contains basic notifier implementations.
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.services.search.service.data.controllers
    Contains the controllers used by the data service.
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.services.search.service.data.jaxrs  
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.synchronizer.api
    Contains APIs for creating components to run in the synchronizer service.
    com.incadencecorp.coalesce.synchronizer.api.common
    Contains abstract implementations of the interfaces along with classes used by the interfaces.
